{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/blog/2024-08-30-how-to-accept-only-number-in-react-input/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aHoisting! To add accept only number in react input, you can use . It will add accept only number in react input. Today, I am going to‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aHoisting!</p>\n<p>To add accept only number in react input, you can use <code class=\"language-text\">type=\"number\"</code>. It will add accept only number in react input.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, how to add accept only number in react input.</p>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import react component.</li>\n<li>Create a Component.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Let‚Äôs start with the first step.</p>\n<h3>Step 1: Install and create a new React app.</h3>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 2: Import react component.</h3>\n<p>After installing, you have to import your React component.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> useState <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 3: Create a Component.</h3>\n<p>You can use <code class=\"language-text\">type=\"number\"</code> to add accept only number in react input.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>h1<span class=\"token operator\">></span>Number Input<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>h1<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>input\n        type<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"number\"</span>\n        value<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>value<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n        onChange<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>handleChange<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n        placeholder<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Enter a number\"</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Add accept only number example.</h3>\n<p>The below code is an example of a React. You have to import <code class=\"language-text\">react</code> and set <code class=\"language-text\">type=\"number\"</code> to add accept only number in react input.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> useState <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">App</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>value<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> setValue<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">useState</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">''</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">handleChange</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">event</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">setValue</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>event<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>target<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>value<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>h1<span class=\"token operator\">></span>Number Input<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>h1<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>input\n        type<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"number\"</span>\n        value<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>value<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n        onChange<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>handleChange<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n        placeholder<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Enter a number\"</span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> App<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">type=\"number\"</code> to add accept only number in react input.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 341px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/f44661e42bfdb6298fe7ba4c5762d8b4/5af35/number.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 69.62025316455697%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRlQAAABXRUJQVlA4IEgAAACQAwCdASoUAA4APtFWpEuoJKOhsAgBABoJYwCdH8ADAl54awJAAPff8754KZj9YfsK92yUflW72ybdzx8zvtSrEYA6qvHtoAA='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, add, only, number\"\n        title=\"React, add, only, number\"\n        src=\"/